##In January, the folk fancy anti-epidemic Grand Award

Micro-signal. Meirirenwu

Functional Introduction, light business, understand life.

Eight key words make up one aspect of the January 2020 outbreak -- how the average person spent this particular month.

In this monthly summary, we decided to capture some of the most ironic bits of news about the epidemic, because these seemingly insignificant slices, make up the real life of everyone in the great event, as if it were hard, but it continues, laughing as much as possible may be the only weapon we have against hardship.

Eight key words make up one aspect of the January 2020 outbreak -- how the average person spent this particular month.

In this monthly summary, we decided to capture some of the most ironic bits of news about the epidemic, because these seemingly insignificant slices, make up the real life of everyone in the great event, as if it were hard, but it continues, laughing as much as possible may be the only weapon we have against hardship.

Planning | the Luoyang team

Face Mask

That's definitely the most important word of January.

A poll on twitter asked: "Can you still buy a mask in Florida? " Nearly 300,000 people voted, 260,000 of whom said they could not.

People who don't have masks and have to go out of their homes have to wear homemade masks to keep out the spray. On January 30, a blogger posted a post on Weibo asking for "the toughest face mask you've ever seen. " So far, the post has attracted 12,000 comments. From these "toughest" face masks, we can get a glimpse of the People's life, mind and wisdom

Some masks are made of fruit shells.

A well-circulated screenshot of a friend's circle shows a 95-year-old man making a mask out of Orange Peel and wearing it to go to a community hospital to get medicine. "He said the mask can be applied with a moist inner layer, while the outer one is beautiful and generous, which can prevent bacterial infection. It can moisten the lungs and has a smell of orange. What a smart old man! I sincerely wish him a long life! " The friend wrote, internet users in Guangxi Province saw an old man near their home, threading a needle through a grapefruit peel and putting it on their face.

A netizen in the supermarket of oneself downstairs, saw literally"hard core"face mask: make with coconut shell face mask, stick to the mouth and nose of the old man.

People make their own "masks" with Orange Peel

Others use plastic sheeting, buckets, raincoats and bags to create masks that may be closer to medical masks in their protective effects than fruit peels, but can feel overwhelming just by looking at the pictures.

People make their own plastic bucket "mask. " Picture / network

Others have had a brainstorm: medical masks are made of disposable nonwoven fabrics, and other things are made of the same material, so why not? And so it became possible to see, diapers, rags, even sanitary napkins on your face. From a hygiene point of view, this is probably the closest thing to the mask itself, although many netizens said, "I really can't get through that. "

The latest news on face masks is that on January 31st, Xiamen began to purchase face masks by appointment lottery. According to the regulations, the registration system is open 24 hours a day, with each person registering once, and the result will be notified by text message. To obtain a mask, one needs to present the original ID card and text message to get the mask.

About the mask, folk wisdom naturally has a humorous side, but most netizens feel sad after laughing: "If the mask is enough, who will wear a fruit skin out? "

Disinfect

You need to wear a mask. You need to sterilize.

January 25, many communities within the spread of "aircraft disinfection" rumors, a few hours later, the rumor. But two days later, on Jan. 27, Mr. Liu, a villager in Heze, Shandong Province, took out his plant protection drone and sprayed the entire village with 84 disinfectants, without any gaps or corners. "It was a rumor, but you made it true, " one netizen commented

According to experts, public space, the elevator is the most vulnerable to cross-infection, therefore, in order to prevent contact infection, many residential elevator carefully equipped with disposable paper towels and instructions: With a paper towel wrapped fingers, press the elevator button and discard the tissue after the ride is over.

January 28, Xi'an City, Shaanxi Province, rural areas, a variety of models of disinfection vehicles directly into the village. There are large decontamination vehicles for plant protection, as well as hand-held decontamination vehicles. In the comment area, some villagers said that the domineering is very domineering, but if not careful, will be sprayed all over.

On January 30, Sichuan mobile users received a text message from the operator reminding them not to neglect to sterilize their mobile phones: sterilize twice a day, go home and immediately sterilize their phones, and use cotton swabs dipped in 75 percent medical alcohol to clean the body, use again after the alcohol has completely evaporated.

On January 31, Uncle Xiao, 64, watched television in Yibin, Sichuan Province, and learned that the outbreak was serious and that his home needed regular disinfection. Just at home have sprayed vegetables remaining dichlorvos for disinfection and epidemic prevention, Xiao uncle thought that dichlorvos can kill insects, perhaps also can kill viruses. So he sprayed some pesticides on the corner of the room and himself, and a few hours later, the dazed uncle Xiao was sent to the hospital by his son. After three rounds of dialysis, he survived.

The doctor who treated Xiao said the organophosphate poison could be absorbed by the body through the airways and skin, and could be replaced with high-grade Baijiu if there was no medical alcohol in the house.

Earthy taste dissuades

After a web of failed attempts to convince disobedient elders to pay attention to the virus, young people are finding that the only way to get stubborn parents to listen is to use a language they know best and can accept.

A poster promoting the aesthetics of the family group has crept up on social media. High Saturation, large font size and use in combination with emoticons, logic forces, and sometimes rhymes:

"The mask word is 13 pictures, Fu Word is 13 pictures, mask word homophonic characters, there is the implication of luck, wear a mask is to wear luck. ".

"The family old man mask wears, the Good Fortune newspaper passes on successively for three generations" .

Users create their own optimus optimus

"The reason why this pneumonia is so severe is because, unlike the traditional ones, it is an alkaline virus. The common bactericidal salts, White Vinegar, and Banlangen are all alkaline and can not be killed at all. The really cheap and useful method is actually hidden nearby. "

Similarly, in the vast rural areas, the simplest approach works best: Village Loudspeakers and Banner Banners are the most sinuous of the propaganda paths.

Through a megaphone, Li Deping, the party secretary of the village of Dachan in Huixian, Henan Province, went viral on the Internet, "Some people are just shameless. If they tell you to stay at home, you can't stay... you're pretty, you're pretty, you're slim... " Li said in an interview, remembering how stressed he was when he became red, many times, he said, don't drop in on me, don't pile up, but some villagers just don't listen. In a fit of anger, he said something heavy, but netizens all said it was the most beautiful Henan dialect they had ever heard.

Outside the loudspeakers, the banners at the mouth of the village are almost the crystallization of the wisdom of civil anti-epidemic, most of them are very particular about the antithesis and rhyme, every sentence sounds.

Some kind advice: "A mask or a vacuum cleaner, you always look at two choices" ; "today visit everywhere, tomorrow pneumonia door" ; "do not dine is to eat later, do not visit is to have relatives later" ;

Some are unforgiving -- "one day they taste wild, the next they meet in Hell" ; "the ones who come out are shameless; the ones who play mah-jongg are"F" Is for Fugitive" ; "the ones who go in to kill one another, the ones who go in to kill themselves" .

Banners in the village

These well-intentioned earthy debarks also serve as a form of lock-in

On January 24, a man from Henan Province came to visit his grandfather on New Year's Day and was rejected by his grandfather. "Put the food in front of the door first! I'll get it myself later. I want to pass the New Year by myself! " As soon as the grandson came out of the corridor, the old man in the mask threw a plastic bag from the window, containing a bag of masks and a red envelope. Then the old man snapped the window shut again.

A man with his wife and children drove 300 kilometers from Nanyang to visit his father-in-law on Jan. 26 in Yanshi, Henan Province. However, the village chief took a photo of the family as if it were going to be one of the most memorable photos in the couple's photo album.

Hard core reporting

In addition to emotional reasoning, some "hard core" measures have also been taken.

On January 27, a girl in Meishan, Sichuan, called the street office and reported her parents who had decided to go out to play cards. Later, the official public account of Chengdu Wuhou police, ping an Wuhou, said parents were welcome to send private messages from backstage to play Mahjong coordinates.

In Shanghai, a boy reported an unlicensed chess room in his neighborhood because his father played cards there all day. Soon, members of the community came to the House and shut down the chess room, he wrote a local rap based on this: This year's New Year's Eve is different, a new type of virus is bound to stick, but some people want Mahjong ten thousand and two don't move, a tube with a tube with two holes, a tube with two tears, two lines with a spring flower in full bloom before going out.

Some young people do not have the heart to report, they took a rather circuitous way. On Jan. 28, Xiao Wu, a 73-year-old man in Ankang, Shaanxi Province, urged his 73-year-old grandfather to drink more at the lunch table to stop his dangerous behavior. Soon, the old man will be drunk, after lunch fell asleep, Xiao Wu also finally relax: GRANDPA finally did not go out!

Drones

For thousands of days, with the aircraft for a time, the UAV in this civil anti-epidemic played a big role.

January 29th, the drone in Hohhot, Inner Mongolia, shouted to an old woman without a mask: "Grandma, don't look, this is our village's drone, you don't go out without a mask, don't run around, remember to hurry home, go home and wash your hands, right? So many people in our village say you, all say but, have to send a drone to fly you."video to the Old Lady turned away from the end of the figure.

The village granny who did not wear a mask was persuaded back by a drone. Image pear video

On the same day, a community official in Yichun, Jiangxi Province, used a drone with an infrared thermal camera to check residents' body temperatures. "If the measured distance can be within one meter, the error rate is 1 percent. "

On January 30, a group of residents playing Mahjong in Penny's town of Jintang County, Chengdu, were just spotted by a drone flying in for inspection, the village cadre's voice comes from the loudspeaker: "Don't pile up! " "The child does not look, hurriedly calls your father and mother to leave

Free of charge

In order to let the people of the country to reduce travel, to help us pass the time, the major platform is also a lot of thought.

On Jan. 24, bytedance announced that the Chinese New Year movie "Lost Mom" would be broadcast free on the Internet. BYTEDANCE paid 630 million yuan to happy media, which also earned the movie a good reputation. However, this reputation slipped away soon after it was released, xu Zheng was embarrassed by Douban's 5.9 rating and by the industry's scepticism.

On January 26, Netease said that in order to successfully help students who have delayed the start of their school year to complete their study tasks during the winter vacation, they will give free online-broadcast classes to all primary and secondary school students in Wuhan. Three days later, all primary and secondary school students across the country are treated the same. A NETIZEN CONCLUDES: tecent donates 300 million, quick hand donates 100 million, netease donates operation.

On January 29, Hownet opened up its collaborative work platform for free, and Weipu opened up the right to download Chinese periodicals for free. The first comment said: "DELETE IT! My tutor is going to see it! "

Boom

In the case of the APP crash, the extent to which the nation has been forced to stay at home this past January has been tied to mobile phones.

On January 25th, the game "peace elite" crashed. This is a hand to eat chicken tour, that day, players log in, suddenly found: play a game to line up number.

On January 27, the multiplayer online gaming platform playbar crashed. The Wolf kills can not open the room, can not start, started the game but does not start... anxious players click on Weibo, want to see if he is the only person who can not play the game, the result directly "play the Bang Bang Bang" on the top of the hot search. Three days later, "play bar and break" hit the hot list in the same way.

On January 29th, the kitchen collapsed. This is the second time since last year's lunar New Year's Eve, when the kitchen was shut down due to too many people learning while watching and learning. Some people say, it seems that today I can only rely on the creative, eat what is left to the gods.

On January 30th, steam crashed. Some Netizens said that the game software as if playing "radish squat" , one after another bang, this is the power of the fat house. As of noon on 1 February, the steam server was still not repaired.

On the same day, Douban collapsed on a weekly basis. But douban users, so used to it, were so unfazed that it wasn't even worth the fuss.

On January 31, Netease opted for a batch of face masks, triggering a stampede by users. In the evening, with less than 10 minutes to go until February, the COVID-19 announced that Shuanghuanglian could suppress the virus. Less than five minutes after the message was sent, all the major drug delivery apps crashed..

On the same day, people who tried to pull fan fiction from the negative news feed found LOFTER dead. When people high on CP found that the web page couldn't load, their first reaction was that the article had been deleted, and when they opened Weibo to ask for help in panic, they found it was just a server crash, so they put their minds down and went to bed early.

It was also on the last day of January, when primary and secondary school students finally decided to start catching up on homework, the online class APP "Shengxue e Netcom" crashed. Can't log in, can't watch the video. Think of the beginning of the teacher to check the progress of online classes, they are very anxious: "Now even do not let me learn it? "

Face Mask

That's definitely the most important word of January.

A poll on twitter asked: "Can you still buy a mask in Florida? " Nearly 300,000 people voted, 260,000 of whom said they could not.

People who don't have masks and have to go out of their homes have to wear homemade masks to keep out the spray. On January 30, a blogger posted a post on Weibo asking for "the toughest face mask you've ever seen. " So far, the post has attracted 12,000 comments. From these "toughest" face masks, we can get a glimpse of the People's life, mind and wisdom

Some masks are made of fruit shells.

A well-circulated screenshot of a friend's circle shows a 95-year-old man making a mask out of Orange Peel and wearing it to go to a community hospital to get medicine. "He said the mask can be applied with a moist inner layer, while the outer one is beautiful and generous, which can prevent bacterial infection. It can moisten the lungs and has a smell of orange. What a smart old man! I sincerely wish him a long life! " The friend wrote, internet users in Guangxi Province saw an old man near their home, threading a needle through a grapefruit peel and putting it on their face.

A netizen in the supermarket of oneself downstairs, saw literally"hard core"face mask: make with coconut shell face mask, stick to the mouth and nose of the old man.

People make their own "masks" with Orange Peel

Others use plastic sheeting, buckets, raincoats and bags to create masks that may be closer to medical masks in their protective effects than fruit peels, but can feel overwhelming just by looking at the pictures.

People make their own plastic bucket "mask. " Picture / network

Others have had a brainstorm: medical masks are made of disposable nonwoven fabrics, and other things are made of the same material, so why not? And so it became possible to see, diapers, rags, even sanitary napkins on your face. From a hygiene point of view, this is probably the closest thing to the mask itself, although many netizens said, "I really can't get through that. "

The latest news on face masks is that on January 31st, Xiamen began to purchase face masks by appointment lottery. According to the regulations, the registration system is open 24 hours a day, with each person registering once, and the result will be notified by text message. To obtain a mask, one needs to present the original ID card and text message to get the mask.

About the mask, folk wisdom naturally has a humorous side, but most netizens feel sad after laughing: "If the mask is enough, who will wear a fruit skin out? "

Disinfect

You need to wear a mask. You need to sterilize.

January 25, many communities within the spread of "aircraft disinfection" rumors, a few hours later, the rumor. But two days later, on Jan. 27, Mr. Liu, a villager in Heze, Shandong Province, took out his plant protection drone and sprayed the entire village with 84 disinfectants, without any gaps or corners. "It was a rumor, but you made it true, " one netizen commented

According to experts, public space, the elevator is the most vulnerable to cross-infection, therefore, in order to prevent contact infection, many residential elevator carefully equipped with disposable paper towels and instructions: With a paper towel wrapped fingers, press the elevator button and discard the tissue after the ride is over.

January 28, Xi'an City, Shaanxi Province, rural areas, a variety of models of disinfection vehicles directly into the village. There are large decontamination vehicles for plant protection, as well as hand-held decontamination vehicles. In the comment area, some villagers said that the domineering is very domineering, but if not careful, will be sprayed all over.

On January 30, Sichuan mobile users received a text message from the operator reminding them not to neglect to sterilize their mobile phones: sterilize twice a day, go home and immediately sterilize their phones, and use cotton swabs dipped in 75 percent medical alcohol to clean the body, use again after the alcohol has completely evaporated.

On January 31, Uncle Xiao, 64, watched television in Yibin, Sichuan Province, and learned that the outbreak was serious and that his home needed regular disinfection. Just at home have sprayed vegetables remaining dichlorvos for disinfection and epidemic prevention, Xiao uncle thought that dichlorvos can kill insects, perhaps also can kill viruses. So he sprayed some pesticides on the corner of the room and himself, and a few hours later, the dazed uncle Xiao was sent to the hospital by his son. After three rounds of dialysis, he survived.

The doctor who treated Xiao said the organophosphate poison could be absorbed by the body through the airways and skin, and could be replaced with high-grade Baijiu if there was no medical alcohol in the house.

Earthy taste dissuades

After a web of failed attempts to convince disobedient elders to pay attention to the virus, young people are finding that the only way to get stubborn parents to listen is to use a language they know best and can accept.

A poster promoting the aesthetics of the family group has crept up on social media. High Saturation, large font size and use in combination with emoticons, logic forces, and sometimes rhymes:

"The mask word is 13 pictures, Fu Word is 13 pictures, mask word homophonic characters, there is the implication of luck, wear a mask is to wear luck. ".

"The family old man mask wears, the Good Fortune newspaper passes on successively for three generations" .

Users create their own optimus optimus

"The reason why this pneumonia is so severe is because, unlike the traditional ones, it is an alkaline virus. The common bactericidal salts, White Vinegar, and Banlangen are all alkaline and can not be killed at all. The really cheap and useful method is actually hidden nearby. "

Similarly, in the vast rural areas, the simplest approach works best: Village Loudspeakers and Banner Banners are the most sinuous of the propaganda paths.

Through a megaphone, Li Deping, the party secretary of the village of Dachan in Huixian, Henan Province, went viral on the Internet, "Some people are just shameless. If they tell you to stay at home, you can't stay... you're pretty, you're pretty, you're slim... " Li said in an interview, remembering how stressed he was when he became red, many times, he said, don't drop in on me, don't pile up, but some villagers just don't listen. In a fit of anger, he said something heavy, but netizens all said it was the most beautiful Henan dialect they had ever heard.

Outside the loudspeakers, the banners at the mouth of the village are almost the crystallization of the wisdom of civil anti-epidemic, most of them are very particular about the antithesis and rhyme, every sentence sounds.

Some kind advice: "A mask or a vacuum cleaner, you always look at two choices" ; "today visit everywhere, tomorrow pneumonia door" ; "do not dine is to eat later, do not visit is to have relatives later" ;

Some are unforgiving -- "one day they taste wild, the next they meet in Hell" ; "the ones who come out are shameless; the ones who play mah-jongg are"F" Is for Fugitive" ; "the ones who go in to kill one another, the ones who go in to kill themselves" .

Banners in the village

These well-intentioned earthy debarks also serve as a form of lock-in

On January 24, a man from Henan Province came to visit his grandfather on New Year's Day and was rejected by his grandfather. "Put the food in front of the door first! I'll get it myself later. I want to pass the New Year by myself! " As soon as the grandson came out of the corridor, the old man in the mask threw a plastic bag from the window, containing a bag of masks and a red envelope. Then the old man snapped the window shut again.

A man with his wife and children drove 300 kilometers from Nanyang to visit his father-in-law on Jan. 26 in Yanshi, Henan Province. However, the village chief took a photo of the family as if it were going to be one of the most memorable photos in the couple's photo album.

Hard core reporting

In addition to emotional reasoning, some "hard core" measures have also been taken.

On January 27, a girl in Meishan, Sichuan, called the street office and reported her parents who had decided to go out to play cards. Later, the official public account of Chengdu Wuhou police, ping an Wuhou, said parents were welcome to send private messages from backstage to play Mahjong coordinates.

In Shanghai, a boy reported an unlicensed chess room in his neighborhood because his father played cards there all day. Soon, members of the community came to the House and shut down the chess room, he wrote a local rap based on this: This year's New Year's Eve is different, a new type of virus is bound to stick, but some people want Mahjong ten thousand and two don't move, a tube with a tube with two holes, a tube with two tears, two lines with a spring flower in full bloom before going out.

Some young people do not have the heart to report, they took a rather circuitous way. On Jan. 28, Xiao Wu, a 73-year-old man in Ankang, Shaanxi Province, urged his 73-year-old grandfather to drink more at the lunch table to stop his dangerous behavior. Soon, the old man will be drunk, after lunch fell asleep, Xiao Wu also finally relax: GRANDPA finally did not go out!

Drones

For thousands of days, with the aircraft for a time, the UAV in this civil anti-epidemic played a big role.

January 29th, the drone in Hohhot, Inner Mongolia, shouted to an old woman without a mask: "Grandma, don't look, this is our village's drone, you don't go out without a mask, don't run around, remember to hurry home, go home and wash your hands, right? So many people in our village say you, all say but, have to send a drone to fly you."video to the Old Lady turned away from the end of the figure.

The village granny who did not wear a mask was persuaded back by a drone. Image pear video

On the same day, a community official in Yichun, Jiangxi Province, used a drone with an infrared thermal camera to check residents' body temperatures. "If the measured distance can be within one meter, the error rate is 1 percent. "

On January 30, a group of residents playing Mahjong in Penny's town of Jintang County, Chengdu, were just spotted by a drone flying in for inspection, the village cadre's voice comes from the loudspeaker: "Don't pile up! " "The child does not look, hurriedly calls your father and mother to leave

Free of charge

In order to let the people of the country to reduce travel, to help us pass the time, the major platform is also a lot of thought.

On Jan. 24, bytedance announced that the Chinese New Year movie "Lost Mom" would be broadcast free on the Internet. BYTEDANCE paid 630 million yuan to happy media, which also earned the movie a good reputation. However, this reputation slipped away soon after it was released, xu Zheng was embarrassed by Douban's 5.9 rating and by the industry's scepticism.

On January 26, Netease said that in order to successfully help students who have delayed the start of their school year to complete their study tasks during the winter vacation, they will give free online-broadcast classes to all primary and secondary school students in Wuhan. Three days later, all primary and secondary school students across the country are treated the same. A NETIZEN CONCLUDES: tecent donates 300 million, quick hand donates 100 million, netease donates operation.

On January 29, Hownet opened up its collaborative work platform for free, and Weipu opened up the right to download Chinese periodicals for free. The first comment said: "DELETE IT! My tutor is going to see it! "

Boom

In the case of the APP crash, the extent to which the nation has been forced to stay at home this past January has been tied to mobile phones.

On January 25th, the game "peace elite" crashed. This is a hand to eat chicken tour, that day, players log in, suddenly found: play a game to line up number.

On January 27, the multiplayer online gaming platform playbar crashed. The Wolf kills can not open the room, can not start, started the game but does not start... anxious players click on Weibo, want to see if he is the only person who can not play the game, the result directly "play the Bang Bang Bang" on the top of the hot search. Three days later, "play bar and break" hit the hot list in the same way.

On January 29th, the kitchen collapsed. This is the second time since last year's lunar New Year's Eve, when the kitchen was shut down due to too many people learning while watching and learning. Some people say, it seems that today I can only rely on the creative, eat what is left to the gods.

On January 30th, steam crashed. Some Netizens said that the game software as if playing "radish squat" , one after another bang, this is the power of the fat house. As of noon on 1 February, the steam server was still not repaired.

On the same day, Douban collapsed on a weekly basis. But douban users, so used to it, were so unfazed that it wasn't even worth the fuss.

On January 31, Netease opted for a batch of face masks, triggering a stampede by users. In the evening, with less than 10 minutes to go until February, the COVID-19 announced that Shuanghuanglian could suppress the virus. Less than five minutes after the message was sent, all the major drug delivery apps crashed..

On the same day, people who tried to pull fan fiction from the negative news feed found LOFTER dead. When people high on CP found that the web page couldn't load, their first reaction was that the article had been deleted, and when they opened Weibo to ask for help in panic, they found it was just a server crash, so they put their minds down and went to bed early.

It was also on the last day of January, when primary and secondary school students finally decided to start catching up on homework, the online class APP "Shengxue e Netcom" crashed. Can't log in, can't watch the video. Think of the beginning of the teacher to check the progress of online classes, they are very anxious: "Now even do not let me learn it? "

The game page crashes, the Netizen is stunned

"The mad king of leisure. "

People who can't get out of their homes because of the epidemic are finally putting themselves in the shoes of the classic question: If you were given a room that was just right, with food, cell phones, and Wi fi, how long could you stay? The answer is that countless people are too busy to panic people have been "crazy emperor" title.

On January 26, the fifth day in Wuhan, Mr. Zhang and his family stayed indoors. In order to alleviate the shoulder and neck pain caused by lying for a long time, Mr. Zhang led a family in the living room square dance. "Now I know why I walk my dog every day. "

On the same day, Mr. Li, a phd student at Tsinghua University in Beijing who was unable to return to his hometown because of the epidemic, told his cat about the function: "I taught you that too, didn't I? You got it all right last time. " The cat wanted to leave several times, were yanked down by Mr. Lee and forced to attend class.
